rComments: After ANT200 do not take her course expecting the same A. She is very less enthused while teaching here and is hard to get a decent grade on the course. Her guidelines are vague. I put more effort into this course than others yet ended up with the lowest grade in this course. If you insist on taking this, use CR/NCR option.

Very good prof, tries to put in as much of her own fieldwork experience as possible which makes the course more relevant. Easy tests, and very straight forward about what she expects. Super approachable and great to take a course with! Loved her!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: She is nice and her class is practically what you would expect out of university. There are only a few tests consisting mainly of lecture material. The tests seem easy if you went to lecture. Did not read the textbook and still aced the tests.
